Secchi (Feet)

column2: Alto cirrus clouds today.  1.9" rain in last 48 hours.  Light northeast winds- very high northeast winds yesterday.  Water temperature is 3 degrees and air temperature is 69 degrees.  Ice off was on April 30- 1992- latest in six years.
Thin overcast- hazy.  The air temperature is 73 degrees and the water temperature is 67 degrees.
Recently received up to 6" of rain.
The water temperature is 70 degrees and the air temperature is 76 degrees.  Brown tint to the water due to over 10" of rain since July 8- 1992.  Highest water level in six years.
The water temperature is 71 degrees and the air temperature is 75 degrees.  Bright sunshine- calm water- very slight green tint- and no zebra mussels seen. best this time of year.
Might have to add more rope!  the water has a slight green tint.  The water temperature is 71 degrees- flat calm waters- and clear skies.  Nicest day this year.
Sunny- slight wave- and high wind.  The water is between green and brown.
Slight breeze- light chop on lake- and two inches above normal- rainfall for month now stands at 3.8.
Sunny- calm- and the air temperature is 70 degrees.
boat traffic heavy. Otherwise calm water- sunny day.
Weather clear with slight wind from North.  Lake level lowest ever seen in recent years as result of draught.  Nothing out at outlet since 7/1.
Wind from N - slight drift S
Water just trickling out at outlet.  Wind from S - drifting N.

Weather clear with slight wind from South.  Water clarity murky as a result of 7 in. of rain in the past week raising water level of Lake to more normal but still on low side.  Test site slightly N of normal.
West wind- water level high- 2 in. of rain last week-
South breeze- buttermilk sky- hazy sun- 1/4 in. rain last night
no wind- clear/sunny- surface very still- no rain last 3-4 days
slight north wind- clear/sunny sky- some ripple- shower last night but no significant rain since 8/2
partly sunny- ripple on surface 5-10mpn NW wind- 0.3 in. of rain yesterday
sunny- surface ripple- 5 mph south wind- no recent rains
Weather cloudy- west wiind less than 5 mph creating surface ripple- no rain in recent days
Weather sunny- north wind less than 5 mph creating slight surfact ripple- no rain recently- lake level below normal
Weather partly sunny with north wind 5-10 mph creating surface ripple.  No rain since last test so lake level low
Weather cloudy- soutwest wind at 10-15 mph so surface ripple- boat drifting badly with wind- several showers last few days- lake level still llow
Heavy mist/overrcast- north wind 10-15 mph- heavy surface ripple/drift- 0.4 in. of rain last 24 hours- lake level still low
Hazy sun with no wind or ripple- no rain so far in Sep. so lake level very low
Partly cloudy- NW wind 5 to 10 mph- surface ripple.water going out outlet. Partly cloudy- NW wind 5 to 10 mph- surface ripple- water flowing out of lake at dam
Overcast- wind 0 to 5 mph from South- slight surface ripple- 1 1/2 in. of rain last night- waer still going out of outle.  Son-in law- Kerry Kirby- confirmed my data.
Partly sunny/overcast- W wind 10 to 15 mph- ripply surface- showers last night-  water still flowing from Lake.  Ralph Owen confirmed data except his secchi depth reading was 19 ft.
Bright overcast- no wind- slight ripple- 0.3 in. of rain about 5 days ago- water barely flowing out of Lake.
Weather-sunny- slight 5 mph wind from north-  slight surface ripple- waves from boaters- no rain in 48 hours- good flow over dam at Lake outlet
Weather--sunny- wind 5-10 mph from north- surface ripply with waves from passing boaters- 1 1/2 in. rain two nights ago
Weather sunny- no wind or surface ripple- no rain since Aug. 2- water flowing over dam at Lake outlet
Weather sunny- 0-5 mph wind from north- slight surface ripple- no significant rain since Aug. 30- water flowing over dam at Lake outlet
Weather sunny- 0-5 mph wind from south- surface ripply- 1/2 in. rain yesterday- flow still going over dam at Lake outlet

Daughter- Steph Kirby- assisted in acquiring data.  Conditions were: hazy sun- 5 to 10 mph wind from south with boat traffic so ripply surface- hot/muggy with thunderstorm activity two nights ago.  Lake level very high after wet spring.

Daughter- Steph Kirby assister-  Weather conditions:  Hazy sus- gusty wind 15 to 20 mph wind from south- boat drifting (no anchor)- very ripply surface- no rain so far this month- but Lake level still high.
Son- Lee danker- assisted.  Weather conditions:  Intermitant sun- wind 5 to 10 mph from west so surface ripply- boat drifting- 0.3 in of rain on 08/03
Weather conditions:  Sunny- wind 5 to 10 mph from south so surface ripply- no anchor so boat drifting- normal water flowing over dam out of Lake.
Weather conditions:  Sunny- wind 5 to 10 mph from west- surface ripply with boat drifting- 1 in. rain last 24 hours- water still flowing over dam.
Daughter Steph Kirby assisted.  Weather condition:  hazy sun- mild S drift- very slight ripple on water surface
Sunny weather- 0 to 5 mph wind from south- surface ripple- some boat traffic- no rain in several days
Overcast- no wind or surface ripple- about 1/8 in. of rain last nite
Sunny with S wind 10 to 15 mph- surface ripple- boat drifting- no rain last 48 hours
Partially sunny- slight S wind- ripply surface- no rain recently- some boat traffic
Heavy overcast- slight N drift- slight ripple- no rain in several days- water level lowest for summer
Intermittent sun/clouds- slight south wind- ripply surface- very heavy pollen recently
Part sun- no wind- ripply surface- very heavy rains recently (7/11--ten plus in.)- Lake level highest ever.
Sunny- 5-10mph south wind- boat traffic/ripply surface- no rain last 48 hours.  Lake level still very high.
Slightly sunny- slight north breeze- surface slightly ripply- no rain last 3 to 4 days- lake level still very high
South wind 5-10 mph- sunny- ripply surface- no boat traffic- no rain last 72 hours.
Sunny- south wind 5 - 10 mph- boat drifting- ripply surface- few showers yesterday.
Sunny- 5-10 mph south wind- no anchor required- no boat traffic--slight surface ripple- no rain last 72 hours.
